Moving into one of the Nevada apartments for rent, will situate you and your family in a dynamic area that affords you ample access to a diverse array of environments that range from unscathed dessert, to blissful domestic suburbs to hustling and bustling cities.There is a slew of great attractions right in your backyard. If you and the family want to indulge in your educational side, take a trip to one of the state's museums. Some notable ones include the Children's Museum of Northern Nevada, Carson Valley Museum, the Eureka Sentinel Museum and the Science Center at the University of Nevada.For a weekend of fun and entertainment, you and your beau can head to Sin City, also known as Las Vegas. There's no better way to illuminate the new chapter in your life than to cruise down the metropolis boulevards basking in neon glow of the roadside signs. You can test your luck at the Mandalay Bay, Caesar's Palace or the Siegel Slots and Suites.If hitting the links is your idea of a good time, then you are in luck - your new Nevada apartment is in close proximity to a slew of great golf courses. These include the Southern Highlands Golf Club, Callaway Golf Center, Rhodes Ranch Golf Club and the Spanish Trail Golf and Country Club.Nevada is also endowed with a rich arts and cultural scene. You and your family will love touring the various galleries and museums such as the Bellagio Gallery of Fine Art, the Duncan Littlecreek Gallery as well as the Nevada Museum of Art located in Reno.Nevada is also situated in close proximity to other great states that you may want to tour after you've finished settling in. Whether you're hitting the open road or jumping on a jet, you will easily be able to journey to Oregon, California and Arizona.Looking for apartments in the Nevada area? Look no further than ApartmentGuide.com to find Nevada apartments for rent and learn more about this neighborhood.Carson City ApartmentsElko ApartmentsFallon ApartmentsFernley ApartmentsHenderson Apartments