Your Guide to Apartments in Alexandria

Are you looking for a fun and vibrant city a stone's throw from Washington, DC? A town rich in history, unique neighborhoods and fine dining? Apartments in Alexandria, VA fit the bill beautifully. You'll never get bored with all the activities and excitement of the city. You might be looking for a one-bedroom apartment near the train station in Old Town or a 3-bedroom apartment with lots of schools and playgrounds nearby, away from the hustle and bustle. Whatever your choices, we are ready at ApartmentHomeLiving.com to present you with the best apartment options in Alexandria that fit your budget, lifestyle and community preferences.You couldn't ask for a better location than Alexandria, VA. You can see the busy city of Washington, DC in the distance, but with its beautiful architecture preserved from the 18th and 19th centuries, Alexandria retains that special character that makes its residents feel at home. You can take a stroll through the Old Town and follow in the steps of George Washington. When finished, you can enjoy the endless culinary options available to residents and visitors.Whatever your lifestyle and apartment requirements, we can help you find the best neighborhood to suit your needs. If you like living near Old Town, you can walk the cobblestones for unique boutique shopping, museums, scary ghost tours and excellent restaurant choices. Besides the Market Square Museum, historic architecture and memorial to George Washington, there's a one-mile long street of outdoor cafes, restaurants and shops. You won't need to depend on the supermarket for your fresh fruit, vegetables, meat and bread if you choose one of the Alexandria apartments near the Old Town Farms Market. If water is more your deal, then you're in great shape because Alexandria is on the Potomac River. You'll appreciate the beautiful scenes and water activities and when you get hungry, you can board a cruise ship for gourmet dining and dancing.We have access to the best Alexandria apartments in every area of the city. No matter which neighborhood you choose, you can enjoy good schools, good neighbors and fine dining options ranging anywhere from local specialty seafood dishes to rustic taverns to traditional Belgian cuisine. If you want to take a leisurely trip over to DC, you have the option of the water taxi. But if you work in DC and need to regularly commute, your best option might be the 15-minute train ride, which you can catch at the station in Old Town Alexandria. Whatever you choose, we are your Alexandria apartment experts!
more...





Alexandria Overview


Alexandria, VA is vivacious and awesome!  The City was awarded in 2016 as one of the top 100 Cities to live in and Top Ten Best Downtown's.  Within the City is “Old Town” and offers the most historically kept part of the City.  Everything you need is so close that it would be ideal to live in an apartment.






Alexandria History


Alexandria, VA was the first European Settlement 1695.  That means there is lot of history in this suburb of Washington DC.  Alexandria, over a century of its birth, the City became a significant port, western side of the Potomac River.  Alexandria lived and died due to the dependency and business of the Potomac River.






Alexandria Weather


The weather in Alexandria provides four awesome seasons.  The summer is perfect with an average high in the 80’s.  Fall brings beautiful foliage with the average temperature of 60 degrees.  Winters are calm, with an average high of 7 inches of snow and 40 degrees. 






Alexandria Media


The city offers plenty of sources to keep updated with the news and music locally.  97.1 WASH FM. WTOP 103.5 FM and HOT 99.5 are a couple of radio stations.  Local TV Stations: ABC-7 and Fox 5dc.   Alexandria Times and the Alexandria Gazette are a couple of the local newspapers.








Alexandria Landmarks


Alexandria, VA is very rich in history and offers literally hundreds of landmarks.  For example, The Carlyle House, Gadsby Tavern, Old Town, which is considered the “Heart of the City”, and George Washington’s Mt. Vernon.  This is just a few locations, the entire City itself is a Landmark.






Things to do in Alexandria


Alexandria has a great night life with many restaurant/bars offering live music every night and due to the close proximity to everything, no need to drive!  Go to Old Town and have a nice dinner while overlooking the Potomac River.






Alexandria Festivals


Alexandria holds so many festivals throughout the year they should consider adding Festival City to the name!  In the fall the City offers a plethora of festivals in older built buildings because of all of the dead people that still live there of course.






Alexandria Vacation spots


Atlantic City!  Only 196 miles gets you to a nice hotel on the beach, where you can obtain your appropriate amount of vitamin D and then take a stroll, just looking at the casinos.  Baltimore, MD is another great place to visit – did you know that is where our National Anthem was penned?








Getting Around Alexandria


Getting around Alexandria is super easy!  Some areas of the city apartments, everything you need is walking distance.  But if walking is not an option and depending on where you want to go you have the options of taking the Free King Street Trolley, Metro rail and bus.






Commuting in Alexandria


There are 3 airports within 10-15 minutes from the city.  There is an Amtrak station, along with the Metro rail.  Of course, there are taxis if you prefer. You will not have to wait long to travel around the city.








Why Here


Why live in Alexandria, VA?  Alexandria feels like living history but living for today.  The amount of history is overwhelming and one never seems to learn everything, there is always something new.  The pride that is taken in caring for and preserving so many historical landmarks is amazing.  The ability to have such diverse options in activities is very important.  One day could be a day spent in Old Town.  The next day spent at the Potomac.  The City is health focused and provides many parks, including dog parks and fitness centers.  And the air is so clean!






Where to move in Alexandria


Where?  “Old Town” is a popular place.  There is always something happening in Old Town and it is just a walk for apartment dwellers.  Old Town North offers an atmosphere of pride it was the first city ever.  The entertainment, the parks, the festivals wrap you in an ambience of warmth.  Taylor Run is another great little spot in Alexandria.   A walk from your apartment takes you to Gadsby’s Tavern Museum, Regional Park, Torpedo Factory Art, Ten Thousand Village Alexandria, Alexandria Archeology and this is naming some sites!  Access to excellent restaurants and shopping.  Another great place to be an apartment dweller. 


















