Apartments for rent in Pennsylvania
Rent an apartment in Pennsylvania and see why the state's motto is "Virtue, Liberty and Independence". Pennsylvania has some of our nation's richest history. But it is also has some of the most modern, forward-thinking cities in the nation. 

How would you like to rent a Pennsylvania apartment in Philadelphia? The city of Philadelphia is positioning itself to become one of the "greenest" cities in the nation. Led by the mayor, the Greenworks Philadelphia project has set lofty goals and put a detailed plan into action that aims to lower city government energy consumption, increase the use of alternative energy sources, lower greenhouse gas emissions and create jobs in green industries, among many other things. There is a combined effort on the part of the city government, local businesses and even the residents to make Philadelphia a greener city and continue to improve its livability.

If you crave the outdoors, Pennsylvania is a great place to rent an apartment. The Allegheny Mountains in the Laurel Highland region have become recognized as a vacation destination, particularly by western Pennsylvania locals and people from the Mid-Atlantic States. Outdoor recreation choices include white-water rafting, lift-served mountain biking, and snow skiing. Of course, The Pocono Mountains is famous for its resorts, natural scenic beauty, 150 lakes, and the quaint, historical towns in the four county area. Pennsylvania has much to offer to the adventurous at heart. 
Consider Pennsylvania apartments in Easton's downtown area if you want to live in a pedestrian-friendly, historic district. Stroll through downtown's historic Centre Square, which was where one of only three readings of the Declaration of Independence on July 8, 1776 took place. From July through October, you can purchase fresh produce and other local goods at the Easton Farmer's Market, which has been held in the Centre Square since 1752. You can also feed your appetite at a local cafe and then browse unique shops and antique stores.
On the hunt for gorgeous Pennsylvania apartments in Pittsburgh? This city has a long history in the steel industry with regional economics, growth and development largely dependent on steel production and trade. Explore this rich history in museums across the city that highlight and preserve what is so distinctly Pittsburgh. The Soldiers and Sailors Memorial Hall honors American War Veterans. There's also the Heinz History Center and the Pennsylvania Trolley Museum, to name just a few.

Pennsylvania has some of the state's most impressive attractions.  There are more wooden coasters than in any other state! Pennsylvania also features a number of pet-friendly apartments and many inexpensive rentals for college students, senior citizens, and families. Browse the wide variety of affordable apartment rentals in Pennsylvania. ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZAbington ApartmentsAkron ApartmentsAldan ApartmentsAliquippa ApartmentsAllegheny ApartmentsAllentown ApartmentsAllison Park ApartmentsAltoona ApartmentsAmbler ApartmentsArdmore ApartmentsAston ApartmentsAudubon ApartmentsAvalon ApartmentsBala Cynwyd ApartmentsBeaver ApartmentsBeaver Falls ApartmentsBellevue ApartmentsBensalem ApartmentsBerwyn ApartmentsBethel Park ApartmentsBethlehem ApartmentsBlandon ApartmentsBloomsburg ApartmentsBlue Bell ApartmentsBoalsburg ApartmentsBoothwyn ApartmentsBreinigsville ApartmentsBrentwood ApartmentsBridgeport ApartmentsBridgeville ApartmentsBristol ApartmentsBrookhaven ApartmentsBryn Mawr ApartmentsButler ApartmentsCamp Hill ApartmentsCanonsburg ApartmentsCarlisle ApartmentsCarnegie ApartmentsChadds Ford ApartmentsChalfont ApartmentsChambersburg ApartmentsChester ApartmentsCheswick ApartmentsClarks Summit ApartmentsClifton Heights ApartmentsClinton ApartmentsCoatesville ApartmentsCollegeville ApartmentsConshohocken ApartmentsCoraopolis ApartmentsCranberry Township ApartmentsCroydon ApartmentsDallas ApartmentsDevon ApartmentsDonora ApartmentsDover ApartmentsDowningtown ApartmentsDoylestown ApartmentsDresher ApartmentsDrexel Hill ApartmentsDublin ApartmentsDuncannon ApartmentsEagleville ApartmentsEast Liberty ApartmentsEast Norriton ApartmentsEast Stroudsburg ApartmentsEaston ApartmentsEdwardsville ApartmentsElizabethtown ApartmentsElkins Park ApartmentsEmmaus ApartmentsEnola ApartmentsErie ApartmentsExton ApartmentsFeasterville ApartmentsFeasterville Trevose ApartmentsFinleyville ApartmentsFolsom ApartmentsFort Washington ApartmentsFreedom ApartmentsGlen Mills ApartmentsGl